# Personal Cheatsheet
# View with: cs or cheatsheet

## Git Shortcuts (from .zshrc)
gs            Fuzzy switch branch (sorted by recent)
gbd           Fuzzy delete branches (Tab for multi-select)
grm           Rebase current branch onto main/master (interactive)
gcm           Checkout main/master and pull
gf            Force push with lease (safer)
lazygit       Git TUI

## jj (Jujutsu)
jj git init           Init new jj repo
jj st                 Status
jj l                  Log: trunk()..@ (commits on current branch)
jj la                 Log: all()
jj d                  Diff
jj ds                 Diff --stat
jj f                  Git fetch
jj p                  Git push

## Neovim

### Quick Access
;             Command mode (instead of :)
kj            Escape (insert mode)
<Esc>         Clear search highlight (normal mode)

### Navigation
C-p           Find files (Telescope)
C-j / C-k     Previous / next buffer
,n            Toggle file tree (NvimTree)
,b            Buffers (Telescope)
gd            Go to definition
gy            Go to type definition
gi            Go to implementation
gr            Go to references

### Search
,fg           Live grep
,fh           Help tags
,gb           Git branch files (changed vs main)
,gs           Git status

### Editing
<CR>          Add new line below (normal mode)
<S-Enter>     Add new line above (normal mode)
<Space>       Insert space at cursor (normal mode)
y             Yank and keep selection (visual mode)
> / <         Indent / outdent and keep selection (visual mode)
,f            Format buffer (conform.nvim)
,tw           Trim trailing whitespace

### LSP
K             Hover documentation
,rn           Rename symbol
,ca           Code action
<Space>a      Open diagnostic float
[d / ]d       Previous / next diagnostic

### Completion (insert mode)
C-Space       Trigger completion
Tab / S-Tab   Next / previous item (or snippet jump)
<CR>          Confirm completion
C-b / C-f     Scroll docs up / down

### Surround (nvim-surround)
ys{motion}{char}   Add surround (e.g. ysiw" wraps word in quotes)
ds{char}           Delete surround
cs{old}{new}       Change surround

### Comments (Comment.nvim)
gc{motion}    Toggle line comment (e.g. gcc for current line)
gb{motion}    Toggle block comment

### Config
,v            Edit nvim config
,z            Edit zshrc
,sv           Source nvim config

### Filetype Notes
- Most web languages: 2-space indent
- Python: 4-space indent
- Markdown/text/rst: spell check enabled
- .html files default to htmldjango

## Yazi (terminal file manager)
y             Open yazi (cd to dir on exit)
a             Create file/directory
r             Rename
d             Move to trash
.             Toggle hidden files
z             Jump via zoxide
<CR>          Open file
/             Search
n / N         Next / previous search result
Tab           Select item
Space         Toggle selection
v             Visual select mode
1-9           Switch tab
t             New tab
q             Quit

## Tmux (prefix = Ctrl-a)

### Sessions & Windows
C-a d                 Detach session
C-a s                 Session picker
C-a c                 New window (in current dir)
C-a 1-9               Go to window N
Shift-Left/Right      Previous / next window (no prefix!)
C-a w                 Window picker

### Panes
C-a | / -             Split vertical / horizontal (in current dir)
C-a h/j/k/l          Navigate panes (vim-style)
C-a C-h/C-j/C-k/C-l  Resize pane (5 units, repeatable)
C-a z                 Zoom pane (toggle fullscreen)
C-a x                 Kill pane

### Copy Mode (vi keys)
C-a [                 Enter copy mode
v                     Begin selection
y                     Copy to clipboard (pbcopy)
Escape                Cancel copy mode
q                     Exit copy mode

### Other
C-a r                 Reload config
C-a C-a               Send literal Ctrl-a

### Settings Notes
- Mouse enabled
- Windows/panes start at 1
- 50,000 line scrollback
- True color enabled

## Atuin (shell history)
Ctrl-r            Interactive fuzzy search (all sessions)
Up arrow          Prefix search from current input
Tab               Insert command (edit before running)
atuin stats       Usage statistics
# Leading space = command not recorded (secrets filter)

## AeroSpace (window manager, prefix = Alt)

### Focus & Move Windows
Alt-h/j/k/l           Focus left/down/up/right
Alt-Shift-h/j/k/l     Move window left/down/up/right

### Layout
Alt-/                  Cycle tiles/horizontal/vertical
Alt-,                  Cycle accordion/horizontal/vertical
Alt-Shift-Space        Toggle floating/tiling

### Workspaces
Alt-1 to Alt-9         Switch to workspace 1-9
Alt-Shift-1 to 9       Move window to workspace 1-9
Alt-a to Alt-z         Switch to workspace A-Z
Alt-Shift-a to z       Move window to workspace A-Z
Alt-Tab                Toggle last workspace
Alt-Shift-Tab          Move workspace to next monitor

### Resize
Alt-- / Alt-=          Resize smart -50 / +50

### Service Mode (Alt-Shift-; or Alt-Shift-r)
r                     Flatten workspace tree
f                     Toggle floating/tiling
Backspace             Close all windows but current
Esc                   Reload config and exit

## Shell
sz            Source .zshrc and confirm
cs            View this cheatsheet
z <dir>       Jump to frecent directory (zoxide)
zi            Interactive directory picker (zoxide)
cat           bat with syntax highlighting
ls / ll       eza listing (ll = long + hidden)
tree          eza --tree
vim           nvim
rg <pattern>  Ripgrep (fast recursive search)

### Environment Tools
mise          Tool version manager (e.g. node lts)
direnv        Per-directory environment variables
# .zshrc.local for machine-specific config
